snippet.textDisplay:
My favourite song since almost a decade (I think this was first season of Coke Studio) ❤️.
Based on the comments, I presume that this is a Bihu song in Assamese language (or some dialect of the same).
I'm a bit lost here - when I shared this song with one of my Assamese acquaintances, she couldn't understand it at all, and said that it is not Assamese (they all speak Assamese within their family).
So:
1. Which is this language exactly?
2. Which is the genre of this folk song?

snippet.textDisplay: This was the best performance in Ep. 2. If you think the instruments don't work well here check out Shankar Mahadevan's Allah Hi Rehem, a wonderful Sufi tune ruined about 1-30 mins. in by a silly guitar riff that's fit for background music in a cooking show. Here, at least the house musicians are trying to create a soundscape that goes with the song.
